      "message": "It can be difficult to repro and depends on the scenario: what I\u0027ve seen so far, if a thread finishes just as we wait, that might result in a hang in WaitForSingleObject:\n\n1. We\u0027re interrupting RamLoader; telling the reader thread with readerWorker() that its time to stop, then calling Thread::wait on it. Sometimes, I get a hang and then gdb says RamLoader is in Thread::wait, but I don\u0027t see the thread entries in gdb for the reader thread anymore.\n2. We\u0027re cleaning up render threads for snapshot load; we\u0027ve told several threads to stop, and then wait on each one in a loop after stopping them. Sometimes, I see Thread::wait for this code, but there is not a single RenderThread active.",
